Description: Privachi is a social networking service allowing the secure sharing of information between individuals.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Privachi is a privacy centric social network designed to put users back in control of their social data. Privachi aims to solve the privacy issues arising from current social networking platforms storing highly contextualized user data and sharing this data with advertisers (for now). Additionally, on current social networking services,  3'rd party applications installed by users find sneaky ways to access and "leak" user's profile.  On Privachi, user's data posted on the service is encrypted such that only the user and his friends can decrypt it. Privachi cannot "listen in" on the conversation. Additionally, Privachi is designed with the belief  that no one service provider should own all of user's data (including Privachi). Privachi provides a mechanism to distribute user's data across his other cloud storage accounts. For example, photo posted on Privachi could be stored in the user's Picasa account, while the comments on that photo is stored in the user's box.net or dropbox account). This results in a distribution of user's context across services, thus, preventing any one service from knowing everything about the user.

Full Description: www.anoncraigslist.org is an email-based service which anonymizes your email address and phone numbers your reply email before it's sent to the posting party in real-time.  Real email addresses and phone numbers are written normally in the body of the reply email. The sender simply adds "anon" infront of the craigslist domain name (i.e., reply-to@gigs.craigslist.org becomes reply-to@gigs.anoncraigslist.org.) Then during the email transfer proces all of the senders known email addresses are replaced with anonymized versions and all phone numbers are replaced with anonymized versions.  The person receiving the response never sees the senders real email address or phone number in the body of the email, yet can contact via email or by phone as usual.

Full Description: MsTRIAL is a compelling, powerful play produced in New York and Los Angeles to enthusiastic audience response, now being adapted to the screen.    ""A Powerful Salvo in Detente Between the Sexes"" -- Los Angeles Times    “It's been weeks and I still think about that play every day. I can’t get it out of my head” -- Board Member, Playwrights Horizons (NYC)    “This play is very much about something” -- Backstage West    ~ An award-quality script previously audience-tested in three live stage productions in tough markets - NYC and Los Angeles    ~ Controversial topic -- workplace sexual assault -- of interest to women's interest groups, a driving force in intelligent film marketing.    Low recovery thresholds and quality scripts offer excellent return opportunities in an expanding film market. The total Production Budget for MsTRIAL is $624,000 (SAG_AFTRA Modified Low-Budget Agreement) offset by ~$125K in pre-sold incentive tax credits and a 50% matching fund commitment ($250K), requiring only an additional $250K to complete financing. The remaining funding of $250K represents a 30% interest in lifetime profits from the film, in addition to the priority return paid to all investors of 115%.    MTP will produce MsTRIAL for 85% less than a comparable studio budget through:    ~ Shooting in Georgia (Savannah), using pre-sold 30% film incentive tax credits to supplement equity. Savannah offers excellent support opportunities based on personal relationships of MTP's principals, Savannah natives with numerous contacts in the area.    ~ Employing a production staff dedicated to the success of the picture, working for less than standard rates.    ~ Employing as yet “undiscovered” but superb talent, so as to produce an exceptional film at lower overall cast cost. “Great films makes stars—not the other way around.”    ~ Shooting on one of several digital film platforms that have allowed independent filmmakers the ability to produce studio-quality films at a fraction of the cost.
